{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"The I\/O Kit is a set of system frameworks and libraries for creating device drivers on Mac OS X, supporting both 32 and 64 bit architectures. Learn about the design of I\/O Kit drivers, as well as tips and tricks for fast, efficient driver development and debugging. Whether you’re bringing a new device to Mac OS X or developing an application to access an existing device, this session is for you.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10-203-IO-Kit-Device-Drivers-for-Mac-OS-X"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc10-203-io-kit-device-drivers-for-mac-os-x"]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC10","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"I\/O Kit Device Drivers for Mac OS X"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2010\/203\/","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","isActive":true}},"references":{"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2010/203/":{"checksum":null,"type":"download","url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2010\/203\/","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict